{"questionId":"26216","questionHtml":"<p>By finding a critical value, perform this test at a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> significance level.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>evidence of multiplying&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>60</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>252</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>252</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;for the <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><br>evidence of finding probabilities around critical region&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for any of these values seen:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>277</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0630518</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>276</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>936948</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>278</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0558415</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>277</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>944158</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>279</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0493055</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>278</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>950694</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><br>critical value&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>279</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>282</mn><mo>≥</mo><mn>279</mn></math>&nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>the null hypothesis is rejected&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(the advertising increased the number of bags sold during the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> days)</p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>. Accept statements referring to the advertising being effective for <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>as long as the <em><strong>R</strong></em> mark is satisfied. For the <em><strong>R1A1</strong></em>, follow through within the part from their critical value.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>evidence of dividing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>282</mn></math> by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math> seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mtext>:</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find critical value using central limit theorem&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>(e.g. sample standard deviation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><menclose notation=\"top\"><mi>X</mi></menclose><mo>~</mo><mi>N</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>, etc.)</p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for a&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0293907</mn><mo>…</mo></math> seen.</p>\n<p><br>critical value&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>63518</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>63518</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>the null hypothesis is rejected&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(the advertising increased the number of bags sold during the&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math>&nbsp;days)</p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>. Accept statements referring to the advertising being effective for <em><strong>A1</strong></em> as long as the <strong>R</strong> mark is satisfied. For the <em><strong>R1A1</strong></em>, follow through within the part from their critical value.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26216","referenceCode":"22M.3.AHL.TZ2.1e.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"By finding a critical value, perform this test at a 5 % significance level.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}